    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1088"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1088">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.622a/37</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1916</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Answering my recent telegrams,
                    my Government cables me that entirely trusting in the information kindly
                    supplied by the United States Government as to the inoffensive and pacific
                    character of the German subjects<note n="1" xml:id="d1088fn1">By another letter
                        of the same day, the word “individuals” was substituted for “German
                        subjects,” thereby including also the Austrians (File No.
                        351.622a/27).</note> recently arrested by the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Descartes</hi>, it has given orders for their immediate release.</p>
                <p>They will be placed under the care of the American Consul at Fort de France.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
